<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="R7-092" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7">
  <metadata>
    <title>Add chat-summarize row to sprk_playbookconsumer table</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <wave>9</wave>
    <estimated-effort>1-2 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>dataverse, wave-9</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>091</dependencies>
    <fr-coverage>FR-17 (data portion)</fr-coverage>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Now that SessionSummarizeOrchestrator routes through IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync (task 091),
    the routing table needs the chat-summarize row to actually map to a playbook. Add a row to the
    sprk_playbookconsumer table in spaarkedev1 with consumer code = "chat-summarize", target
    playbook reference (the playbook currently fronted by WorkspaceOptions.ChatSummarizePlaybookId),
    and match conditions. Use MCP Dataverse tooling preferred; PowerShell migration script fallback.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior Dataverse / platform developer familiar with sprk_playbookconsumer schema,
    IConsumerRoutingService consultation pattern, and the MCP dataverse tooling.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A single sprk_playbookconsumer row exists in spaarkedev1 such that:
    1. sprk_consumercode (alternate key, string) = "chat-summarize" — matches ConsumerTypes.ChatSummarize constant in BFF.
    2. sprk_playbookid (lookup to sprk_analysisplaybook) = the playbook GUID currently configured in
       WorkspaceOptions.ChatSummarizePlaybookId (resolve at task-execution time by reading
       config/{env}.json or appsettings.json).
    3. sprk_matchconditions (JSON column) = empty / null / "{}" (chat-summarize has no
       conditional routing — it always dispatches to the same playbook). Document this decision.
    4. The row is in spaarkedev1 (development environment); test + prod tenant rollout handled
       separately under NFR-07.
    5. Verification: invoke IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync("chat-summarize") via a quick
       integration test or REPL-style smoke and confirm it returns the playbook ID without falling
       back to WorkspaceOptions (which would indicate the row isn't found).
    6. Idempotency: re-running the row insertion must NOT create duplicates — use upsert semantics
       on sprk_consumercode alternate key.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="orchestrator">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SessionSummarizeOrchestrator.cs</file>
    <file purpose="consumer-types">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PublicContracts/ConsumerTypes.cs</file>
    <file purpose="routing-service">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PublicContracts/IConsumerRoutingService.cs</file>
    <file purpose="canonical-doc">docs/architecture/ai-architecture-consumer-routing.md</file>
    <file purpose="config-source">config/spaarkedev1.local.json (or equivalent — for ChatSummarizePlaybookId)</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">Caching — IConsumerRoutingService has 5-min TTL; row insertion will be picked up after cache expiry. If immediate verification needed, restart BFF App Service or wait 5 min.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-17">Acceptance criterion: chat-summarize consumer row in sprk_playbookconsumer table.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-04">No new invalidation hook — accept the 5-min TTL delay for cache pickup.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-07">Rollout scope — spaarkedev1 only in this task. Customer-tenant migration handled separately.</constraint>
    <constraint source="MUST NOT modify">docs/architecture/ai-architecture-consumer-routing.md — READ-ONLY in R7 per spec (chat-routing-redesign-r1 owns).</constraint>
    <constraint source="MUST NOT create">docs/data-model/sprk_playbookconsumer.md — owned by chat-routing-redesign-r1 follow-on per spec.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §11">Component justification triple:
      1. Existing: sprk_playbookconsumer table already exists (chat-routing-redesign-r1 promoted it to first-class). 6 rows for existing consumers already present (per design.md §11).
      2. Extension: this task adds ONE row using the existing schema. NO new column, NO new table.
      3. Cost-of-doing-nothing: IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync("chat-summarize") returns null; SessionSummarizeOrchestrator falls back to WorkspaceOptions.ChatSummarizePlaybookId on every call (graceful-degrade fallback works but R7 FR-17 acceptance criterion not met).
    </constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>ai/consumer-routing</topic>
    <files>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-014-caching.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/ai-architecture-consumer-routing.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/dataverse-mcp-usage/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/dataverse-create-schema/SKILL.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="MCP dataverse create_record" location=".claude/skills/dataverse-mcp-usage/SKILL.md">
        Preferred path: mcp__dataverse__create_record with sprk_playbookconsumer entity.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="PowerShell Web API fallback" location="scripts/dataverse/Add-EntityNameValidatorNodeTypeOption.ps1">
        R4-era pattern if MCP is unavailable. Idempotent via Get-then-Create.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      sprk_playbookconsumer was promoted to first-class status by chat-routing-redesign-r1. The
      table currently has 6 rows for existing consumers (per design.md §11). chat-summarize is the
      7th — added now because task 091 just refactored SessionSummarizeOrchestrator to call
      IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync("chat-summarize"). Until this row exists, the orchestrator
      falls back to WorkspaceOptions.ChatSummarizePlaybookId on every call (the graceful-degrade
      pattern chat-routing-redesign-r1 task 028d established).
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="091" status="required">SessionSummarizeOrchestrator must already consult IConsumerRoutingService — if 091 isn't done, this row has no consumer.</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>R7 task 094-096 (Wave 9) — wire Playbook Library modal into consumer surfaces. Those tasks consult sprk_playbookconsumer for the consumer listing.</item>
      <item>R7 task 067 (Wave 6) — author docs/guides/ai-guide-consumer-wiring.md uses chat-summarize as a case study.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL · 📋 REASON: dataverse schema/data modification in production-adjacent environment (spaarkedev1), idempotency required, blocking dependency for downstream wave tasks · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context">
      Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md (FR-17 + NFR-04 + NFR-07) + plan.md (Wave 9) + ai-architecture-consumer-routing.md.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Verify dependency">
      Confirm task 091 is complete — SessionSummarizeOrchestrator calls IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync("chat-summarize").
      Confirm row absence first via Dataverse query (mcp__dataverse__read_query or PowerShell).
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Resolve target playbook ID">
      Read config/spaarkedev1.local.json (or App Service appsettings in Azure) for WorkspaceOptions.ChatSummarizePlaybookId.
      Confirm the playbook exists in sprk_analysisplaybook (query by sprk_playbookid alternate key).
      Document the GUID in task notes for traceability.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Describe sprk_playbookconsumer entity">
      Run: mcp__dataverse__describe to confirm column names + types: sprk_consumercode (string), sprk_playbookid (lookup), sprk_matchconditions (string or memo).
      Note any required-flag fields beyond these three.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Insert the row (preferred: MCP)">
      Run: mcp__dataverse__create_record with payload:
      {
        "entity": "sprk_playbookconsumer",
        "data": {
          "sprk_consumercode": "chat-summarize",
          "sprk_playbookid@odata.bind": "/sprk_analysisplaybooks({resolved-playbook-guid})",
          "sprk_matchconditions": null
        }
      }
      OR (fallback): write a script scripts/dataverse/Add-ChatSummarize-Consumer-Row.ps1 using Web API + upsert-on-alternate-key semantics. Script must be idempotent (re-run safe).
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Verify row created">
      Run: mcp__dataverse__read_query against sprk_playbookconsumer where sprk_consumercode = 'chat-summarize'.
      Assert: exactly 1 row; sprk_playbookid matches the resolved GUID.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Cache-aware verification">
      The IConsumerRoutingService cache TTL is 5 min (ADR-014, NFR-04). To verify the row is picked up:
      - Option A: wait 5 min then trigger a chat-summarize call via SprkChat UI and observe BFF logs
        for the resolved playbook ID (should match the new row's GUID, not the WorkspaceOptions fallback).
      - Option B: restart BFF App Service in spaarkedev1 dev environment to force cache refresh, then
        trigger a chat-summarize call.
      Document which option was used + the verification result.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Idempotency check">
      Re-run step 5 (MCP create_record or PowerShell script). Confirm it does NOT create a duplicate
      (the platform's alternate-key upsert semantics or script Get-then-Skip should prevent duplicate).
      If duplicate created, halt + investigate alternate-key configuration on sprk_consumercode.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Document migration step">
      Append to projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/handoffs/dataverse-changes.md (create if not exists)
      a row entry: date, table, action ("insert sprk_playbookconsumer chat-summarize"), GUID values,
      operator. This is the traceability record for the wave-9 dataverse changes.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `/code-review` on any PowerShell script (if fallback used).
      Run `/adr-check` against ADR-014 (caching TTL preserved) + spec NFR-04 (no new invalidation logic).
      Verify no test/code changes accidentally bundled.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
      Mark task 092 status complete; advance current-task.md to task 093.
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Commit">
      Commit any script + traceability notes with conventional message.
      Example: chore(r7/wave9): add chat-summarize row to sprk_playbookconsumer in spaarkedev1 (task 092, FR-17)
      NOTE: if pure MCP insertion with no script, commit may only include notes/handoffs/dataverse-changes.md and TASK-INDEX update.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>Read (config files + canonical doc + spec)</tool>
    <tool>mcp__dataverse__describe (confirm entity schema)</tool>
    <tool>mcp__dataverse__read_query (verify absence then verify presence)</tool>
    <tool>mcp__dataverse__create_record (preferred row insertion)</tool>
    <tool>Write (PowerShell script fallback, traceability notes)</tool>
    <tool>Bash (git commit)</tool>
    <tool>Skill (code-review at Step 9.5 — script only)</tool>
    <tool>Skill (adr-check at Step 9.5)</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="dataverse-row">sprk_playbookconsumer row with sprk_consumercode = "chat-summarize" in spaarkedev1</output>
    <output type="optional-new-file">scripts/dataverse/Add-ChatSummarize-Consumer-Row.ps1 (only if PowerShell fallback used)</output>
    <output type="new-or-updated-file">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/handoffs/dataverse-changes.md (traceability entry)</output>
    <output type="state-update">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/current-task.md (advance to task 093)</output>
    <output type="state-update">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md (mark 092 ✅)</output>
    <output type="commit">chore(r7/wave9): add chat-summarize row to sprk_playbookconsumer in spaarkedev1 (task 092, FR-17)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Row exists in sprk_playbookconsumer with sprk_consumercode = "chat-summarize"</criterion>
    <criterion>sprk_playbookid lookup points to the playbook GUID configured in WorkspaceOptions.ChatSummarizePlaybookId</criterion>
    <criterion>sprk_matchconditions = null/empty (chat-summarize has no conditional routing — documented in task notes)</criterion>
    <criterion>Insertion is idempotent — re-running does NOT create a duplicate (verified)</criterion>
    <criterion>Post-cache-refresh, IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync("chat-summarize") returns the new row's playbook GUID (not falling back to WorkspaceOptions) — verified via BFF log inspection OR App Service restart + chat-summarize smoke</criterion>
    <criterion>Traceability entry in notes/handoffs/dataverse-changes.md</criterion>
    <criterion>code-review + adr-check pass at Step 9.5 (FULL rigor) — ADR-014 TTL preserved, no new invalidation logic per NFR-04</criterion>
    <criterion>current-task.md updated to point at task 093 as next</criterion>
    <criterion>TASK-INDEX.md shows 092 ✅, 093 🔲 ready</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
